cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite both the article from preferred-citation and the software itself."
title: "PET-FM-Bench: A Pre-Registered Cross-Foundation-Model Benchmark on Nuclear-Medicine Imaging Tasks with Systematic Contamination Audit"
abstract: "Pre-registered cross-foundation-model benchmark on nine downstream nuclear-medicine imaging tasks. Evaluates five published FMs (FMCIB, CT-FM, BiomedCLIP, RAD-DINO, DINOv2) plus a 10-seed random-initialisation control against an IBSI-compliant pyradiomics baseline (MIRP) using frozen-embedding linear or Cox probes. Includes a 54-cell (FM × task) contamination audit with five-tier confidence schema and an Amendment A13 calibration sub-study (Brier, calibration intercept and slope, ECE, reliability diagrams; Kaplan–Meier observed survival per decile of predicted survival for Cox tasks). Deterministic at SEED = 42. Pre-registered on OSF; thirteen amendments (A1–A13) logged before affected analyses ran."
